About 11 persons in Lagelu Local government area of Oyo State have lost their lives to Cholera in the council.
 
The interim council chairman, Kelani Abdullai, explained that the cholera outbreak was first recorded at Ariku village, with five persons killed, before spreading to Lagun village, where six persons also died as a result of complications from the deadly acute infectious disease.
 
Abdullai said his immediate action is to investigate the cause of the cholera outbreak, which has been traced to lack of access to potable water.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .